{% if backend.static_capable %}
## Static site — no backend

This project is configured for static-output rendering (`{{ backend.framework }}`).
There is no application-side backend code; the rendered output is a tree of
static assets served by a CDN. Sections that describe server-side
concerns (Routes / Data models / Authentication) are intentionally omitted
because they don't apply to the static-site shape (v2.1.6 BL-349). If you
later move to a server-rendered mode (Astro `output: 'server'`, Next.js
without `output: 'export'`, etc.), re-run `/lp-define` to regenerate this
document with the server framing.
